# Sign Language Detection with DETR

Train a DETR model for sign-language symbol detection from webcam-captured data.

## Setup
1. Install UV: `pip install uv`
2. Clone repo: `git clone https://github.com/nicknochnack/SignDETR .`
3. Install dependencies: `uv sync`

## Configure Classes
Edit `src/config.json`:
- `dataset_root`: dataset folder to read/write (example: `data_10class`)
- `classes`: ordered class names
- `colors`: one RGB color per class

`train.py`, `test.py`, and `realtime.py` now infer class count directly from `src/config.json`.

## Fast Data Collection (No Label Studio Required)
Use automatic palm detection and auto-label writing:

```bash
uv run src/utils/collect_images.py --images-per-class 150 --camera-id 0
```

What this does:
- Detects palm/hand region using MediaPipe.
- Captures only when hand is detected, stable, and sharp.
- Writes image + YOLO label automatically.
- Saves directly into `{dataset_root}/train|test/images|labels` from `src/config.json`.

Controls during capture:
- `n`: next class
- `p`: previous class
- `space`: manual save for current class
- `q`: quit

If your environment has a stripped MediaPipe build (missing `mp.solutions`), the script automatically falls back to an OpenCV skin-based detector.

## Optional Label Studio
Label Studio can still be used later, but it is optional in this workflow.

## Training
1. Create checkpoints folder:
```bash
mkdir checkpoints
```
2. Train:
```bash
uv run src/train.py
```

## Inference
1. Test set inference: update checkpoint path in `src/test.py`, then run:
```bash
uv run src/test.py
```
2. Real-time inference: update checkpoint path in `src/realtime.py`, then run:
```bash
uv run src/realtime.py
```

## Reference
- [DETR Colab walkthrough](https://colab.research.google.com/github/facebookresearch/detr/blob/colab/notebooks/detr_demo.ipynb)
